Summary of Material Information:

  • Legislative Impact on Longroad Energy (Infratil subsidiary):
  • Tax Credit Eligibility:
    • Extended safe-harbor window (12 months vs. 60 days) and PIS deadlines (4–5 years vs. ~2.5 years).

  • FEOC Rules:
    • Applies only to projects starting construction after 31 December 2025.

  • Battery Storage: Phase-down delayed to 2034, but FEOC rules pose challenges for Chinese-reliant projects.

  • Longroad has 2.6GW safe-harbored (up from 1.8GW in May).

  • First Solar partnership mitigates FEOC risks for solar projects.

  • Executive Order Risk:

  • Potential narrower interpretation of safe-harbor rules (Treasury guidance due in 45 days).

  • Market Tailwinds:

  • Strong demand from data centers, electrification, and domestic manufacturing supports long-term growth.

Material Information Summary – Challenger Gold (ASX: CEL)

Key Highlights (Metallurgical Testwork & Heap Leach Potential)

  • Heap Leach Viability Confirmed:
  • Gold recoveries up to 85% (average 75%) from low-grade mineralization (as low as 0.15 g/t Au), surpassing global averages (typically 55–79%).
  • Silver recoveries: Average 41%.

  • Crush size: Optimal recovery at ½ inch crush size.

  • Lithology Impact:

  • Dacite: 66–87% Au recovery (0.1–1 g/t Au).
  • Lutite: 64–91% Au recovery (0.2–1 g/t Au).

  • Calcite-hosted material showed weaker recovery (~10% of mineralization).

  • Economic Transformation:

  • 74.3 Mt of material (previously considered waste) now potentially viable, containing 2.9 Moz AuEq.
  • Potential to expand mine life and scale vs. prior Scoping Study (7.2 Mt plan).

PFS Progress

  • Final metallurgical testwork on track for early Q4 2025 completion, including:
  • Sequential Flotation optimization.
  • PFS-level comminution tests.
  • Large-diameter Column Leach scale-up.

Strategic Implications

  • Heap leach circuit could significantly enhance project economics by processing low-grade halo material.
  • Potential shift to larger open-pit scenario (vs. underground in Scoping Study), lowering unit costs.

Next Steps

  • Panel 4: Larger-diameter (6") column tests to simulate commercial-scale heap leaching.

Note: No capital raising, financials, or material corporate actions announced. Focus is on technical and operational milestones for the Hualilan PFS.

Material Information Summary: Drilling Update (Perpetual Resources Ltd, ASX: PEC)

Key Highlights Relevant for Trading/Capital Markets:

  • 200m continuous LCT pegmatite intersected at Target 1 (Igrejinha Project, Brazil), open in all directions, with potential for caesium (pollucite) and lithium (spodumene) mineralisation.
  • Potential high-value caesium discovery: Visual observations and pXRF readings suggest pollucite presence (globally rare, strategic mineral). Assays pending (first results expected mid-July).
  • Historic high-grade samples:
  • Rock chip samples: Up to 7.6% Li₂O and 41.5% Cs₂O (pXRF spot readings; not lab-confirmed).
  • 1m channel sample: 3.26% Li₂O.
  • New regional target identified: Untested pegmatite with 300m strike length in southeast license area.
  • Drilling progress: 750m completed (of 1,500m program); completion expected late July.

Cautionary Notes:

  • pXRF and visual mineral estimates are non-definitive; assays required for validation.
  • Pollucite (caesium) potential could position PEC as a rare global explorer in this commodity, pending lab results.

Next Catalyst: Initial assay results (mid-July).
